description:
&lt;p&gt;Sutton Health and Care is a pioneering partnership made up of the GP federation in Sutton, the London Borough of Sutton, South West London and St George’s Mental Health Trust and Epsom and St Helier hospitals. Working together, we provide community services in Sutton, caring for adults in their own homes across the borough.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an enthusiastic Band 7 Practice Educator to join us in our community nursing services within the London borough of Sutton. You will be an experienced nurse who is committed to training and developing others and to making a real difference to our community nursing teams. You will be passionate about community nursing and the implementation of high standards and quality care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a role model and skilled communicator, you will motivate and influence staff, working together to build and maintain a dynamic learning environment&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are a passionate, motivated team player and want to excel in supporting a team of healthcare professionals in the delivery of exceptional holistic healthcare to a diverse patient group, supported by a multidisciplinary team of community specialists’ nurses and district nurse, we want to hear from you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Previous experience of community nursing is essential. We offer clinical supervision and access to learning and development to support your continuous professional development. We encourage community nurses with an interest in education to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The pioneering partnership of Sutton Health and Care is truly exciting, and together, we can achieve more for the people we care for. We want local people to receive the care that they need in the right environment. Bringing together our expertise will allow us to improve patient care and will enable local people to access the right support, care and treatment more easily than ever before.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We encourage informal visits.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Shirley Forson&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title: Operational manager for Cheam and South Sutton PCN and Podiatry&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: shirley.forson@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number: 07584 777 122&lt;/p&gt;
